        "content": "<p>fitzgen <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12691#issuecomment-3975385288\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12691\">issue #12691</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You need to configure with <code>-W threads=n</code>/<code>config.wasm_threads(false)</code> when pre-compiling the Wasm if you want to run that pre-compiled Wasm with <code>-W threads=n</code>/<code>config.wasm_threads(false)</code>. Wasmtime will not keep track of which Wasm features a binary actually uses, only which Wasm features were enabled at compilation time.</p>\n</blockquote>",
